        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>191. Telegram 729 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d191fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–1555. Confidential;
                        Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-15"
                            >September 15, 1955, 11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d191-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d191-1"/>
                <p>729. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Word “conferences” in last sentence paragraph 4 my telegram 726 should be
                    corrected read “conference”, that is singular not (repeat not) plural.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Note: FE Message Center notified 9/15/9:36 a.m. EMB (CWO)</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
